      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL FELIX (5) has shown good improvement at his last two starts, hitting the frame latest when 2nd at Maitland over 450m. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. One of the contenders. MRS. MINIVER (2) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 3.5 lengths into second (30.91) at Taree Super Track in a Grade 5 over 525m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings four times from seven starts. Deserves a win and gets her chance. SIGHT AND SOUND (1) was prominent throughout when winning in one of the fastest times of the card two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 5th and beaten 7 lengths at this track (30.15). Key runner who gets her chance to atone. ACE'S FOUR BRIAN (4) comes into calculations after placing at this track and distance most recently.",
